  "2026-07-08T17:07:58.712Z",claude-code-agent,"Verification evidence: full coverage passed at 100/100/100/100 (5462 tests), lint/static/docs/contracts gates passed, and packed-install temp proof passed in /tmp/pm-agent-ux-proof-TYSgf1 for pm list --today, pm list --recent, pm contracts --summary, and SDK runAction({action:'contracts', options:{summary:true}})."
  "2026-07-08T17:41:48.923Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence update: CI Gates (static) failed because the committed contract snapshot was generated before rebuilding dist after tool-parameter metadata copy changes. Rebuilt with pnpm build, regenerated with pnpm contracts:update, and reran the full static CI sequence locally: pnpm version:check && pnpm changelog:pm:check && pnpm contracts:check && pnpm security:scan && pnpm lint && npm pack --dry-run. Result: passed."
  "2026-07-08T18:04:30.103Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence: addressed latest bot feedback before repush. Fixed SDK/MCP search contract leakage by keeping list-only --today/--recent out of search schemas, added help to contracts summary intents, treated programmatic updatedAfter:null as unselected, and clarified open-only today docs. Verification passed: focused tests (78 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5463 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T18:23:03.068Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed the final Gemini normalizer finding by making normalizeExtensionFlagName accept unknown, ignore null/blank values, trim valid strings, and reject non-string values with a deterministic TypeError. Added focused coverage. Verification passed: focused tests (79 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5464 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T18:49:39.068Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed final Gemini edge cases by ignoring blank updatedAfter values in list window conflict detection and adding more core command intents (guide, ops, reindex, focus, telemetry) to contracts summary output. Verification passed: focused tests (79 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5464 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T19:17:16.127Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed CodeRabbit schema feedback by expanding the shared summary parameter description to include health rollups and adding contracts action schema mutual-exclusion rules for projection flags. Verification passed: focused tests (80 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5465 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T19:39:00.635Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed Greptile pushed-review schema/runtime mismatch by adding action-schema mutual-exclusion rules for list today/recent/updatedAfter windows across list variants. Verification passed: focused tests (81 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5466 tests)."
  "2026-07-08T20:07:39.271Z",claude-code-agent,"Review evidence update: addressed final value-sensitive schema feedback by making schema mutual exclusion conditional on selected boolean values, adding completion summary intent, and rejecting bare '-' short extension flags. Verification passed: focused tests (81 tests), CI-equivalent static sequence, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 (5466 tests)."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T10:48:18.168Z",maintainer-agent,"Agent/developer-experience program map (2026-07-11, maintainer directive: drastically improve pm CLI DX; documentation-only pass). This epic owns CLI-side DX; this note is the ledger — extend it on future DX asks, never re-brainstorm.\n\nDX FOR THIS TOOL = what an agent pays per task: tokens read, retries burned on flag/shape traps, commands memorized. Three existing lanes already carry most of it:\n1. GRAMMAR (epic pm-n7rr + ADR pm-pbyu + shim pm-0z7n + baseline pm-a22j): 65 top-level commands -> ~12 noun clusters, shared verb vocabulary, one-screen help target. The census/sequencing notes on pm-n7rr are the plan of record.\n2. TOKEN SHAPE (this epic's children): pm-cfed lean JSON (+48-53% vs TOON today), pm-g9xk lean errors, pm-ishm repeated-tags bloat, pm-nilh 12.7x mutation echo; pm-vxxm contracts --summary SHIPPED as the agent bootstrap path.\n3. TRAP ELIMINATION: NEW pm-srns (filed today) = uniform format-flag grammar + single envelope spec across every command; pm-gdi7 unknown-option suggestions; pm-p3x4 .activity decoy; pm-a9mc validate counts-only.\n\nSHIPPED DX wins (fence — never re-file): PR#502 caller-aware next/held_by_others + claim --next; pm-b84u repeated --ac accumulates; pm-zazb dep-shorthand fail-fast with hint; pm-2ldo hybrid search quoting; pm-1h7w priority range hint; pm-fy8o invalid-type hint; comments --body/--comment aliases.\n\nCANDIDATE LEVERS (gated on pm-a22j token baseline numbers; promote to items only with evidence):\na. Golden agent-transcript replay — measure tokens-per-completed-task on recorded agent sessions, not per-command; makes DX regressions CI-visible (extends pm-cu1i gate, never a new harness).\nb. Machine-readable deprecation channel — when the 0z7n shim rewrites an alias, envelope carries the canonical spelling so agents self-migrate (pm-0mox counters are the read side).\nc. Exit-code contract — uniform semantic exit codes documented in the envelope spec (pm-srns's spec is the home; today create/update failures hide under pipes).\nd. First-run agent orientation — `pm contracts --summary` + `pm next` as the documented two-call cold-start; belongs in docs + plugin templates, not new commands.\nREJECTED (constraints, not oversights): no new top-level commands for DX features (grammar rule: flags on existing nouns, pm-plwm precedent); no interactive/TUI affordances on the agent path; no output redesign outside the pm-srns/pm-cfed envelope spec (one spec, not per-command taste)."
