body: "## Charter\nLiving capability epic for the CLI command surface and agent ergonomics: lifecycle primitives (create/update/close/claim/next), bulk operations, query filters, hierarchy views, output projections, and never-block error UX. pm is agent-first: every command must be usable by an agent with zero out-of-band context, and every error must carry a machine-actionable recovery path.\n\n## Scope\n- In: command surface additions/refinements, flag ergonomics, output formats (toon/json/csv/table), never-block guidance, did-you-mean suggestions, agent token-efficiency of outputs.\n- Out: MCP tool surface (pm-5k4v), storage/history internals (pm-o2kc), extension-owned commands (pm-ugqx).\n\n## Status\n97 closed children delivered the v0.1 surface (next, focus, plan family, update-many, list projections, close structured fields, shortcuts, aliases). This epic stays OPEN as a living backlog per the capability-epic convention — new command-surface work lands here.\n\n## Open children (2026-07-04)\n- pm-qt5d — --pm-path package install leaks extensions into caller workspace (path-scoping safety).\n- pm-gdi7 — unknown-option flag suggestions, list-closed projection, schema add-field help discoverability.\n- pm-b3e9 — pre-install package-owned command names should hint the owning install command.\n\n## Update 2026-07-05\nNew initiative epic parented here: **pm-n7rr — CLI surface simplification** (noun-verb consolidation, ~60 -> ~15 top-level commands, zero feature loss). Children: pm-a22j token baseline, pm-0z7n alias shim layer, pm-pfqi list-* consolidation, pm-tqel history namespace, pm-tnud package namespace, pm-eq4x lifecycle sugar fold, pm-o3fh calendar sugar to builtin-calendar, pm-6apl ops namespace, pm-e2bq tiered contracts-driven help, pm-1kxs agent story. Grammar ADR: pm-pbyu (under pm-m2u1).\n\n## Update 2026-07-06\nComposability contract set filed here (stated product principle: pm composes with grep/jq/xargs for on-the-fly complex queries): pm-m9xv persona story, pm-646c NDJSON output mode for list/search/context, pm-psy1 test-gated scripting contract (exit codes, stdout/stderr discipline, field-name stability). Related existing items: pm-kipd stdin JSON create/update, pm-cfed lean JSON."
